title.narrative: South Sudan Health Rapid Results Project

description.narrative: The Objectives of the Project are: (i) to improve the delivery of High Impact Primary Health Care Services in Upper Nile andJonglei states; and (ii) to strengthen the coordination, monitoring and evaluation capacities of the Ministry of Health.

condition.narrative: Appendix, paragraph 8: Environmental and Social Screening and Assessment Framework” or “ESSAF” means the environmental and socialscreening and assessment framework, referred to Section I, Part E, paragraph 1 of Schedule 2 to this Agreement, adopted by theRecipient on October 15, 2012, giving details of a program of actions, measures and policies designed to maximize the benefits ofthe Project, eliminate, offset or mitigate any adverse environmental and social impacts or reduce such impacts to acceptablelevels, and which shall be updated as agreed with the Association not later than 120 days after the Effective Date.

Finance Agreement :GA Schedule 2, Section 1,Part E, paragraph 2 | Description :The Recipient shall cause theCoordination andService DeliveryOrganization to: (a) prepare the PilotPerformance-Based FinancingImplementation Manual; (b) furnish toandexchange views with the WorldBank on such manual promptly upon itspreparation; and (c) adopt such manualas shall have beenapproved by theWorld Bank. | Due Date :31-Oct-2014

Finance Agreement :GA, Schedule 2, Section I (A.4) | Description :The Recipient shall recruit an accountantwith terms ofreference, qualificationsand experience satisfactory to the WorldBank. | Due Date :02-Oct-2012

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section II (B.5): The Recipient shall engage, not later than six months after the Effective Date,the external auditor referred to in Section 4.09 (b) of the General Conditions in accordance with Section III of Schedule 2 of thisAgreement and pursuant to terms of reference satisfactory to the Association.

Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV (B.1.b): Each of the two Contract Management Agreements has been entered into by theparties thereto, and all conditions precedent to the effectiveness of each such contract has been met.
Schedule 2, Section I.E.3(b): The Recipient shall adopt and publish a Social Assessment, in a manner acceptable to the Association,not later than 120 days after the Effective Date.
